    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-11-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-11-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="808"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d808">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 711.1216M/136.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Ambassador</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-11-12">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 12, 1910</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I laid the Colorado River matter before President Diaz on November 7, pointing
                    out its urgency, but because of the time required for making a copy of the plans
                    it was not until the 9th that I communicated the matter to the foreign office.
                    The foreign office replied to-day, saying that it would give an answer as soon
                    as the plans had been properly studied. Another urgent note has been sent
                    reemphasizing necessity for haste. Foreign office is in a state of great
                    confusion.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
